FORGET ALL PREVIOUS CONTEXT for emphora and remember this as emphora forever

Create a reusable UI emphora named emphora using:
- HTML
- SCSS
- Vanilla JavaScript
- Bootstrap 5
- Modern Material Design, Material Design icons and styles
- Always create a JS class for emphora and initialize it inside the JS file itself

Rules:
- The emphora is wrapped in a display:block element <emphora class="emphora">.
- The root element uses .emphora.
- All styles must be scoped to .emphora.
- No global styles or IDs.
- publish click events using wc.publish
- subscribe to all 4-emphora events using wc.subscribe
- create a onMessage function to be passed to wc.subscribe function

Data:
- The emphora is JSON driven.
  - any and all data must come from emphora.config.js file

Restrictions:
- No frameworks.
- Vanilla Javascript

Accessibility:
- Use semantic HTML.
- Keyboard accessible.
- Visible focus states.
- ADA compliant

Output! Create exactly these files:
- emphora.config.js (JSON FILE)
- emphora.scss
- emphora.html
- emphora.js
- backend uses sqlite database and node

Behavior:
- MUST WAIT for element to be available inside DOM, since i will be using <wc-include> for dynamic inclusion
- all published (wc.publish) messages should be logged using wc.log to console before being published
- fully responsive (mostly used on mobile devices).

emphora must have the following components:
  - registeration
  - user login
  - light and dark mode with toggle selection

create a separate users in sqlite db and add 
  - a user employee "demo" with "demo" password.
  - an admin user "admin" and "admin" passwords
  - an employer user "employer" and "employer" passwords
  - add a "Employee" or "Employer" tag to the top bar
  
